{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\nrebar's LOCAL ticket-store write path commits one git object graph per event (~3.3\ncommits/event on the `tickets` branch). This is the git-issue-style high-bloat pattern;\nthe durable way to bound growth is to create fewer objects at the source — the git-bug\n`operationPack` pattern (multiple ops serialized -> one commit). Supersedes orphan e3d0\n(sleek-bur-train) and folds duplicate 39c5 (grungy-grain-drawl). Discovered from the\nclosed bounded-git-growth epic 97e7, which addressed *reclaim* (stock gc) but left the\n*growth rate* at write time out of scope.\n\n**SCOPE (corrected — the original text was stale).** This epic is about the LOCAL ticket\nstore write path ONLY (`src/rebar/_store`). The Jira **reconciler**\n(`src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/`) is OUT OF SCOPE — the original \"WS-B3: reconciler\nbatch-apply\" line was a mis-scoped artifact and is DROPPED. The reconciler's inbound path\nis a REFERENCE only (proof the batch pattern is safe in this codebase — same store, same\nlock, same canonical bytes): `inbound_translate._write_event_file` writes an event file\nunder the write lock WITHOUT committing per-event, and the run commits the accumulated\nfiles in a batch. We do NOT modify the reconciler; the new primitive lives in `_store` and\nis index-based (atomic-rename + `git add` + one `git commit`), mirroring the existing\nsingle-event `stage_and_commit`. (We deliberately keep the porcelain add+commit-against-\nthe-shared-index mechanism rather than a detached-GIT_INDEX_FILE plumbing variant, so the\nbatch path reuses `stage_and_commit`'s exact lock/rebase-guard/unmerged-recovery code and\nstays byte-identical; no second write mechanism to maintain.)\n\n**Why batching is invariant-safe (verified).** Replay, dedup, union-merge convergence, and\nSNAPSHOT compaction all key off each event's per-event UUID, NOT commit boundaries\n(`reducer/_replay.py`, `_cache.py`, `_commands/compact.py`). So collapsing N commits into 1\nis invisible to readers as long as each event stays its own uuid-named file (invariant I2)\nand the single locked writer (I5) is preserved.\n\n**Already shipped (do NOT rebuild).** The importer (`src/rebar/_io/import_ndjson.py`)\nalready has idempotency-by-`source_id` (`_scan_existing_source_ids`) and deferred-push (it\nsets `REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off` and does one final push). What remains is that it still commits\none-per-event: its passes call `rebar.create_ticket`/`edit_ticket`/`link`/`comment`, each\nof which flows `composer.create_core`/`_commands/_seam.py::append_event` ->\n`event_append.write_and_push` (one lock + one commit per call). Those two seam functions\nare the real per-event-commit bottleneck, NOT `import_ndjson.py` alone.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- A batch-commit write primitive exists in `_store` and is adopted on the importer's\n  bulk path, reducing commit count on a synthetic many-event import to `ceil(events /\n  chunk_size)` commits (a >=10x reduction at the default chunk of 256), with no regression\n  to replay, dedup, union-merge convergence, or SNAPSHOT compaction.\n\n## Workstreams\n- **B1** — `_store.batch_stage_and_commit(items)` where `items` is a sequence of\n  `(ticket_id, event_dict)`. Acquire the write lock ONCE (it is NOT re-entrant, so B1 must\n  NOT loop `stage_and_commit`); validate + canonical-stage every event BEFORE the lock;\n  then holding the lock, atomic-rename each temp into its I2 path, one `git add`, ONE\n  `git commit`. All-or-nothing: any failure (validation, rename, add, non-recoverable\n  commit) unstages AND unlinks ALL already-placed paths (not just the failing one) — the\n  single-path `_unstage`/`_silent_unlink` helpers are looped over every path. The\n  `_recover_from_unmerged` helper is generalized to re-add the FULL list of batch paths on\n  retry (re-adding one would drop the other N-1). Add a batched `write_and_push` variant\n  (one push after). Single-event path unchanged (the reversibility guarantee: the importer\n  can fall back to per-event writes by not calling B1).\n- **B2** — adopt B1 on the importer's INDEPENDENT passes (Pass 1 CREATE, Passes 2a–2d\n  parents/links/file-impact/comments). Bridge the interface gap explicitly: add a\n  compose-ONLY seam (a variant of `create_core`/`append_event` that RETURNS the composed\n  `(ticket_id, event_dict)` without committing), buffer the composed events per pass, and\n  flush each buffer through `batch_stage_and_commit` in chunks. Chunk size default = 256,\n  hard-coded (NO new config key — single consumer, no second call-site). Pass 2e\n  (statuses) is STATEFUL (children-before-parents, `cascade=False`) → left per-event.\n- **B4** — benchmark + crash-resume. A synthetic N-event import asserts commit count drops\n  from ~N to `ceil(N/256)`. A malformed event mid-chunk must trigger whole-chunk rollback\n  (no partial commit). A simulated crash mid-batch (kill before commit) must leave either\n  the whole batch's commit or none; the next run's `source_id` re-scan skips already-\n  committed events and re-emits the rest — proving partial-batch recovery. Named regression\n  suites that must stay green: `tests/unit/test_store_batch_write.py`, the replay/dedup/\n  union-merge tests under `tests/unit` + `tests/interfaces/store`, and the SNAPSHOT\n  compaction tests.\n- **(optional stretch)** — cascade transition/claim batching (parent-first cascade emits\n  one commit per ancestor; stateful, medium risk). Note only; build only if B1/B2 land\n  easily.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `_store.batch_stage_and_commit(items)`: one lock acquire, N uuid-named event files (I2), one commit; single-event write path unchanged\n- [ ] All-or-nothing rollback: on any failure ALL already-renamed paths are unstaged from the index AND unlinked from the worktree; `_recover_from_unmerged` re-adds the full batch path list on unmerged-recovery retry\n- [ ] Batched `write_and_push` variant (one push after the batch commit)\n- [ ] Importer adopts B1 via a compose-only seam: independent passes (1, 2a–2d) buffer composed events and flush through B1 in 256-event chunks; Pass 2e (statuses) stays per-event\n- [ ] Commit-count reduced to `ceil(events / 256)` on a synthetic many-event import (before/after benchmark asserts a >=10x reduction), exercised via a real import run producing a real tickets branch\n- [ ] No regression: `tests/unit/test_store_batch_write.py`, replay/dedup/union-merge convergence, and SNAPSHOT compaction tests green\n- [ ] Crash-resume test: partial-batch recovery leaves whole-commit-or-none and the source_id re-scan resumes cleanly; a malformed-event-mid-chunk test proves whole-chunk rollback\n- [ ] Docs updated: the `docs/scale-envelope.md` \"no batched-commit fast path\" assertion is corrected, and an ADR captures the batch-commit decision, the I2/I5 invariants it preserves, and the deliberate reconciler-path exclusion"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783648720933586001,"uuid":"e45a7e57-f1c3-4d65-acac-0ffaa0696730"}